timeline.bodyText:
Bringing in an ExecutorService etc. seems rather heavy handed for a single thread. How about just going with:
Thread extractThread = new Thread(() -> { ... }, "ExtractThread");
extractThread.join(parseDuration);
extractThread.interrupt();
I'm assuming that interrupt() will be sufficient, as that's they typical recommendation for ExecutorService.shutdownNow(). But maybe you had issues?

